If we look at Africa the same custom recurs. Thus what was taken at Agrigentum, and in the battle of Cannae, and elsewhere, was sent to Carthago.

Among the ancient Franks, as we learn from Gregory of Toum, what was captured was divided by lot 3 and the king had nothing of the booty but what the lot gave him.
